The paper discusses a computational approach to fact checking using a knowledge graph, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.DB (Databases), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Among these, cs.AI and cs.CL are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the use of natural language processing and machine learning in the paper. However, cs.DB, cs.IR, and cs.LG are also relevant, as they involve database management, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques, respectively.
